      "summary": "Core runtime boundaries rely on oversized callback bags, creating low-cohesion abstractions with weak compile-time contracts.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/startuporchestrator/startup_orchestrator.go",
        "goseg/importer/importer.go",
        "goseg/shipworkflow/operations_runtime.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`startupInitRuntime`/`StartupRuntime` aggregate many unrelated callbacks (init, host, storage, background service concerns) behind one merged struct and validation by tag groups.",
        "`importerRuntime` embeds three runtime structs and exposes many callback fields; behavior contracts are validated at runtime through `seams.NewCallbackRequirementsWithGroups(...)` instead of narrow compile-time interfaces.",
        "`workflowRuntime` mixes event publication, transition policy, sleep/timing, DNS resolution, ship ops, config ops, and upload orchestration in one dependency object."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Split runtime bags into use-case-scoped interfaces/constructors (e.g., startup init, startup background, import upload, import provision, workflow transition emit). Replace string-tag group validation with typed constructor requirements so missing dependencies fail at compile time where possible.",
      "confidence": "high",
      "impact_scope": "codebase",
      "fix_scope": "architectural_change",
      "root_cause_cluster": "runtime_bag_overgeneralization"
    },
    {
      "dimension": "abstraction_fitness",
      "identifier": "mutable_global_broker_boundary",
      "summary": "Event broker abstraction is undermined by mutable package-global defaults, hiding dependency direction and creating order-dependent behavior.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/importer/importer.go",
        "goseg/shipworkflow/operations_runtime.go",
        "goseg/startuporchestrator/startup_orchestrator.go",
        "goseg/docker/events/events.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`importer` and `shipworkflow` each hold a package-global default broker plus `SetDefaultEventBroker(...)` mutation points guarded by mutexes.",
        "Startup wiring mutates these globals during initialization (`InitializeImporterFn` in startup runtime), so correctness depends on initialization sequence.",
        "`events.NewGlobalDefaultBroker()` delegates through mutable process-default runtime lookups on each call, reinforcing implicit global indirection."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Make broker dependencies explicit in constructors and pass them through runtime instances end-to-end. Remove package-level setter mutation for production paths and reserve globals only for legacy compatibility wrappers.",
      "confidence": "high",
      "impact_scope": "subsystem",
      "fix_scope": "architectural_change",
      "root_cause_cluster": "implicit_global_runtime_state"
    },
    {
      "dimension": "abstraction_fitness",
      "identifier": "pass_through_runtime_factories",
      "summary": "Runtime factory layers add indirection but little behavioral value, increasing call depth and maintenance surface.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/docker/orchestration/runtime_defaults.go",
        "goseg/main.go",
        "goseg/config/runtimecontext/context.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`runtime_defaults.go` has many helpers that primarily forward package functions into function fields (`runtimeFileOps`, `runtimeContextOps`, `runtimeNetdataOps`, `runtimeMinioOps`, `defaultRuntimeSnapshot`, etc.) with minimal policy.",
        "`main.go` introduces wrapper methods (`bootstrapRuntime.bootstrap`, `.startServer`, `.runC2CCheck`) that mostly nil-check and forward to stored callbacks.",
        "`runtimecontext/context.go` adds getter/setter wrappers over a global pointer state, and these are then re-wrapped again through orchestration runtime op structs."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Collapse pure pass-through wrappers where no policy/testing seam is needed; keep only seams that enforce behavior (timeouts, retries, fallback rules, translation). For remaining seams, centralize them in a smaller number of domain adapters instead of many per-function factories.",
      "confidence": "medium",
      "impact_scope": "subsystem",
      "fix_scope": "multi_file_refactor",
      "root_cause_cluster": "runtime_bag_overgeneralization"
    }
  ],
